SIMPLE: mercurification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mercurification
<hw>Mer*cu`ri*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mercurification</ets>. See <er>Mercurify</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>The process or operation of obtaining the
mercury, in its fluid form, from mercuric minerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The act or process of
compounding, or the state of being compounded, with mercury.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurify</ent>⟦br⟧
